PART 8: SPECTRAL RECURRENCE — EIGENVALUES OF SKEW MATRIX
========================================================================

S = A - A^T (skew-adjacency), eigenvalues ±iλ_k
det(I+2A) = det(J+S) where J=all-ones
Eigenvalues of S are pure imaginary: ±iλ_1, ±iλ_2, ...
How do eigenvalues change under deletion?

